<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
  <title>Debriefing</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="page-center">
    <div class="card">
      <h1>Thank You for Your Participation!</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">We would now like to tell you the true purpose of this study.</p>
      <div class="debrief-text">
        <p>This study actually investigates whether <strong>the experience of "outsourcing" or "delegating" tasks to AI affects people's preferences for physical activity in everyday life</strong>.</p>
        <p>Our hypothesis is that when people delegate cognitive tasks to AI, it activates an "effort-minimising mindset" that may generalise from the cognitive domain to the physical domain, making people more inclined to choose physically effortless options.</p>
        <p>In this study, half of the participants were asked to <strong>delegate tasks to an AI assistant</strong> (experiencing "AI did it for me"), while the other half were asked to <strong>evaluate the quality of AI-generated answers</strong> (experiencing "I'm judging AI's work"). Both groups saw identical AI output, but the psychological roles were entirely different.</p>
        <p>The English word completion task measured your implicit cognitive state, and the "lifestyle preference survey" measured your tendency to choose physically effortless options.</p>
        <p>We did not disclose the full purpose at the start in order to capture your natural responses. We sincerely apologise for this necessary deception.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <p style="font-weight:600;color:#333;">If you now know the true purpose and would prefer your data <strong>not</strong> to be used, please select below. Your data will be deleted, and this will not affect your compensation.</p>
      <div class="choice-group mt-16">
        <div class="choice-option" onclick="selectConsent(this,'yes')">
          <div class="choice-dot"></div>
          <span class="choice-text">I consent to my data being used</span>
        </div>
        <div class="choice-option" onclick="selectConsent(this,'no')">
          <div class="choice-dot"></div>
          <span class="choice-text">I wish to have my data deleted</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <button class="btn btn-primary btn-full mt-16" id="finishBtn" disabled onclick="submitDebrief()">Finish Study</button>
    </div>
  </div>
  <script>
    var pid = '<%= pid %>';
    var consent = null;
    function selectConsent(el, val) {
      consent = val;
      document.querySelectorAll('.choice-option').forEach(function(o){o.classList.remove('selected');});
      el.classList.add('selected');
      document.getElementById('finishBtn').disabled = false;
    }
    function submitDebrief() {
      fetch('/api/debrief',{method:'POST',headers:{'Content-Type':'application/json'},body:JSON.stringify({pid:pid,consent:consent})})
      .then(function(r){return r.json();}).then(function(d){if(d.next)window.location.href=d.next;});
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
